<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="245" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1071,1350]" pageId="14" pageNumber="245">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,1251,1277]" pageId="14" pageNumber="245">Comment:</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[391,489,1251,1277]" pageId="14" pageNumber="245">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Friese" authorityYear="1901" box="[533,899,1251,1278]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="xanthocnemis" subSpecies="ardesiaca">
<emphasis box="[533,899,1251,1278]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="245">Centris xanthocnemis ardesiaca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a female of 
<taxonomicName box="[1082,1272,1251,1278]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthocnemis">
<emphasis box="[1082,1101,1252,1278]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="245">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1118,1272,1251,1277]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="245">xanthocnemis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with blackish pubescence on the mesosoma. This feature is very variable in both sexes, a fact related with the numerous junior synonymies of this species (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." box="[510,722,1323,1350]" pageId="14" pageNumber="245" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref22678" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis box="[591,641,1323,1349]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="245">et al</emphasis>
., 2007
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
